N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 7000.2 - Complaints

State Regulations

The commission shall receive, initiate, investigate and
hear complaints against any judge with respect to the judge's qualifications, conduct, fitness to perform, or the performance of the judge's official duties. Prior to commencing an investigation of a complaint initiated by the
commission, the commission shall file as part of its records an administrator's
complaint. Notes
